American Chinese food uses a chemical called MSG, which has garnered a bit of a nasty reputation
Some people claim they have a sensitivity or allergy to MSG, but this is actually utter bullshit!
MSG, or monosodium glutamate, is an almost pure extract of umami, which is a flavor present in things like meat and mushrooms

"Chinese restaurant syndrome" was made up by a small group of people with strong racist and xenophobic sentiments, and the idea unfortunately spread :^[
